listitem.para:
@property Verbose: Controls the verbosity of the underlying C++ I/O operations.

@Verbose.getter Verbose(self): Returns True if verbose output is enabled, False otherwise.

@Verbose.setter Verbose(self, bool val): Sets the verbosity. True enables verbose, False disables it.

@property EnablePyAMI: Controls whether PyAMI (ATLAS Metadata Interface) integration is enabled for metadata processing.

@EnablePyAMI.getter EnablePyAMI(self): Returns True if PyAMI is enabled, False otherwise.

@EnablePyAMI.setter EnablePyAMI(self, val): Sets the PyAMI state.

@property MetaCachePath: Manages the file path for caching metadata.

@MetaCachePath.getter MetaCachePath(self): Returns the metadata cache path as a Python string.

@MetaCachePath.setter MetaCachePath(self, val): Sets the metadata cache path.

@property Trees: Manages the list of ROOT tree names to be read.

@Trees.getter Trees(self): Returns a list of tree names as Python strings.

@Trees.setter Trees(self, val): Sets the tree names. Accepts a single string or a list of strings.

@property SumOfWeightsTreeName: Manages the name of the ROOT tree that contains the sum of weights information.

@SumOfWeightsTreeName.getter SumOfWeightsTreeName(self): Returns the sum of weights tree name as a Python string.

@SumOfWeightsTreeName.setter SumOfWeightsTreeName(self, str val): Sets the sum of weights tree name.

@property Branches: Manages the list of ROOT branch names to be read.

@Branches.getter Branches(self): Returns a list of branch names as Python strings.

@Branches.setter Branches(self, val): Sets the branch names. Accepts a single string or a list of strings.

@property Leaves: Manages the list of ROOT leaf names to be read.

@Leaves.getter Leaves(self): Returns a list of leaf names as Python strings.

@Leaves.setter Leaves(self, val): Sets the leaf names. Accepts a single string or a list of strings.

@property Files: Manages the list of ROOT file paths to be processed.

@Files.getter Files(self): Returns a list of valid ROOT file paths as Python strings. It calls self.ptr.check_root_file_paths() to validate paths.

@Files.setter Files(self, val): Sets the ROOT file paths. Accepts a single string or a list of strings. It clears existing files if val is empty and then validates the new paths.
